Adam Frackowiak's 12 Rules of Wu Wei from his article "I Stopped Swimming Upstream" (Medium, Jan 2026):
 1. Accept Your Flaws (Stop Fixing Yourself) — your "flaws" are part of your nature; observing without judgment saves energy
 2. Trust Your Intuition — stop strangling every decision with logic; let life surprise you
 3. Live in the "Radical Now" — be fully present in whatever you're doing
 4. Practice Aggressive Patience — things unfold on their own timeline
 5. Stop the "Worry Loop" — worrying is a rocking chair: gives you something to do but gets you nowhere
 6. Relinquish Control Over the Uncontrollable — focus energy only on what you can influence
 7. Work for Joy, Not Escape — don't use busyness to avoid deeper issues
 8. Be Open to Others (The Flexible Mind) — stay adaptable and receptive
 9. Don't Dwell on the Past — it's already gone
10. Honour Your Vitality — respect your energy limits
11. Embrace Simplicity — complication is the enemy of flow
12. Learn the Art of "Letting Go" — open your hand to hold the world